The paper proposes a framework for modeling vehicle interactions at uncontrolled intersections using game theory, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed approach also accounts for traffic rules and geometries, which suggests relevance to the sub-categories of control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses simulation results and computational complexity, which may relate to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG).
